00:02:41,995 --> 00:02:44,622
BATES MOTEL
PARKING LOT

4
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,634
Nice move.

5
00:02:56,926 --> 00:02:59,929
-You're cold, so go inside and warm up.
-Okay, let's do that.

6
00:03:00,346 --> 00:03:01,181
By yourself.

7
00:03:15,778 --> 00:03:16,821
Hello.

8
00:03:18,406 --> 00:03:19,282
My gosh.

9
00:03:20,158 --> 00:03:22,952
You're both soaked.

10
00:03:23,745 --> 00:03:25,914
For one night or just for a few hours?

11
00:03:29,209 --> 00:03:30,793
-Well--
-Which room do you want?

12
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:32,837
The mirror room? The themed room?

13
00:03:32,921 --> 00:03:33,922
-Or costumes?
-No.

14
00:03:34,964 --> 00:03:35,798
Well...

15
00:03:38,259 --> 00:03:39,260
Come here.

16
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:41,930
Come here. Come on.

17
00:03:44,015 --> 00:03:45,475
-Do you want any add-ons?
-Sorry?

18
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:47,560
A love chair? A vibrating bed?

19
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:50,188
How about handcuffs or a whip?

20
00:03:51,439 --> 00:03:53,816
I'll give you ten percent off
if you pay cash.

21
00:03:55,109 --> 00:03:56,110
Let's go.

22
00:03:56,194 --> 00:03:58,363
How about a whirlpool tub?
Don't tell anyone--

23
00:03:58,446 --> 00:03:59,781
-Come on. Let's go.
-No.

24
00:03:59,864 --> 00:04:01,032
I like this place.

25
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,661
Come on. I'll take you home.

26
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:07,872
-I don't want to freeze to death.
-Our rooms are steamy hot.

27
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:12,377
-Do you live far from here?
-That's not the point.

28
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:15,129
Why bring your motorcycle
in this torrential rain?

29
00:04:15,838 --> 00:04:18,675
-Then just take a taxi home.
-Give me money for the ride.

30
00:04:19,717 --> 00:04:21,261
Hey, don't tell me--

31
00:04:21,344 --> 00:04:24,389
Right. I didn't bring anything.
Not even my wallet and phone.

32
00:04:25,014 --> 00:04:26,307
Then if I hadn't come--

33
00:04:26,391 --> 00:04:29,435
I would've walked all night in the rain,
like a crazy woman.

34
00:04:30,186 --> 00:04:33,773
Can you please think before you act?
Don't be so impulsive and reckless.

35
00:04:34,941 --> 00:04:37,110
Anything can happen
on that dark, remote road.

36
00:04:37,193 --> 00:04:39,988
How could you keep walking
all by yourself? You're fearless.

37
00:04:41,072 --> 00:04:42,615
If something bad happened...

38
00:04:48,037 --> 00:04:49,038
Why are you mad?

39
00:04:49,455 --> 00:04:51,291
Who cares if I walk all night

40
00:04:51,374 --> 00:04:53,126
or put on a strip show in the rain?

41
00:04:53,876 --> 00:04:54,961
Why are you upset?

42
00:04:56,671 --> 00:04:58,214
Were you worried about me?

43
00:04:59,465 --> 00:05:00,675
Are you upset?

44
00:05:02,552 --> 00:05:03,845
Does your heart ache?

45
00:05:09,934 --> 00:05:10,768
Do you...

46
00:05:12,812 --> 00:05:13,896
like me?

47
00:05:18,985 --> 00:05:22,363
Well, I'm asking
because I really have no clue.

48
00:05:22,905 --> 00:05:23,865
You know that.

49
00:05:23,948 --> 00:05:27,201
You'd better not act like you know
and understand everything about me

50
00:05:27,493 --> 00:05:29,662
when you know nothing.
Don't be delusional.

51
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:32,290
You're all empty inside.

52
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:34,500
You're just loud.

53
00:05:35,543 --> 00:05:36,544
Like an empty can.

54
00:05:36,627 --> 00:05:40,840
I'm an empty can who won't understand
how you feel until the day I die.

55
00:05:44,385 --> 00:05:45,720
What do you feel now?

56
00:05:47,096 --> 00:05:47,930
Tell me.

57
00:05:50,892 --> 00:05:52,101
Why are you all quiet?

58
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:54,145
Are you an empty can too?

59
00:05:58,900 --> 00:05:59,901
I...

60
00:06:02,278 --> 00:06:03,112
I...

61
00:06:04,113 --> 00:06:05,073
Just say it.

62
00:06:11,037 --> 00:06:11,871
"I love you."

63
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:14,749
We'll get a room.

64
00:06:18,294 --> 00:06:19,128
Just...

65
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:21,756
Any clean and warm room would do.

66
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:23,174
It's 50,000 won.

67
00:06:32,016 --> 00:06:33,476
What? You have no money?

68
00:06:35,603 --> 00:06:36,687
What about your phone?

69
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,107
Even my mom has to pay on the spot.

70
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:40,024
Bye.

71
00:06:45,363 --> 00:06:47,281
I guess you ran out in a hurry

72
00:06:47,782 --> 00:06:50,243
that you couldn't think before you acted.

73
00:06:54,163 --> 00:06:54,997
It's okay.

74
00:06:55,581 --> 00:06:57,708
It's natural for men to act instinctively.

75
00:06:58,209 --> 00:06:59,168
Go start your bike.

76
00:07:07,885 --> 00:07:08,719
Hey.

77
00:07:11,013 --> 00:07:14,434
There's a cheap motel down the street.

78
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:16,811
They let you pay later. Go there.

79
00:07:19,188 --> 00:07:20,189
-Thank you.
-Sure.

80
00:07:27,613 --> 00:07:31,742
CHAPTER 5
RAPUNZEL AND THE CURSED CASTLE

81
00:07:52,054 --> 00:07:52,889
Get off.

82
00:08:01,856 --> 00:08:03,649
