88
00:08:26,589 --> 00:08:28,341
This reminds me of an animal stall.

89
00:08:29,050 --> 00:08:32,136
Don't you feel like
you're a domesticated animal living here?

90
00:08:36,140 --> 00:08:37,642
What? Was that rude?

91
00:08:38,726 --> 00:08:39,644
Go get changed.

92
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:43,481
-Where's your brother?
-Downstairs.

93
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,484
-Don't call him over.
-I won't.

94
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,862
-I don't want you around him.
-Are you jealous?

95
00:08:50,446 --> 00:08:52,615
Don't go near my brother, ever.

96
00:08:53,032 --> 00:08:54,784
-Is this a warning?
-Whatever it is.

97
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:58,621
-Just leave him alone.
-Will he want the same thing?

98
00:09:00,581 --> 00:09:01,999
I should ask him directly.

99
00:09:04,835 --> 00:09:06,337
What? What's the matter?

100
00:09:07,672 --> 00:09:09,131
What's with that gaze?

101
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:13,386
-What does my face tell you?
-You're handsome.

102
00:09:14,136 --> 00:09:16,472
-No, my facial expression.
-You look obnoxious.

103
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:19,433
I'm talking about my mood, emotions,
and the state I'm in.

104
00:09:19,517 --> 00:09:20,434
Not interested.

105
00:09:24,021 --> 00:09:27,066
Take a look at their faces
and try to read their emotions.

106
00:09:27,316 --> 00:09:28,818
Learn it, even if you don't care.

107
00:09:29,485 --> 00:09:32,363
If you don't like to feel the emotions,
just memorize them.

108
00:09:33,072 --> 00:09:35,658
Make an effort
unless you want to live alone forever.

109
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:39,120
-I don't want to. Why should I?
-You should still do it.

110
00:09:42,415 --> 00:09:44,000
I'm not autistic.

111
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:46,919
-I'm just--
-You're not the zombie kid either.

112
00:09:47,587 --> 00:09:50,006
The kid with no emotions,
but only the desire to eat.

113
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:53,467
Do you think what he wanted
was to satiate his hunger?

114
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:57,054
Or someone's warmth?

115
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:00,808
What do you think the answer is?

116
00:10:01,642 --> 00:10:04,020
Food? Was satisfying his desire
all that mattered?

117
00:10:20,202 --> 00:10:21,037
Warmth.

118
00:10:22,913 --> 00:10:25,875
This is what he truly wanted.
He didn't want to be just fed.

119
00:10:27,001 --> 00:10:29,420
-You wanted to impart that message.
-You're wrong.

120
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:32,214
-I'm wrong?
-You're wrong. Food was all that mattered.

121
00:10:32,673 --> 00:10:34,425
He's a zombie, so he has no emotions.

122
00:10:34,717 --> 00:10:37,136
He wanted a full belly
even if it was his mom's limbs.

123
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:39,847
"Warmth"? Bullshit.

124
00:10:40,014 --> 00:10:43,184
That's just the sickening pity
of sentimentalists like yourself.

125
00:10:43,476 --> 00:10:44,644
You got it all wrong.

126
00:10:46,604 --> 00:10:49,940
I'm hungry. Give me something to eat.
Before I chew off your limbs.

127
00:11:10,544 --> 00:11:11,837
Who's pitying whom?

128
00:11:22,014 --> 00:11:24,141
WHEN USING THE SHAMPOO, PUMP THREE TIMES

129
00:11:25,726 --> 00:11:27,103
SANG-TAE

130
00:11:30,564 --> 00:11:33,025
WHEN BRUSHING TEETH,
DON'T GO OVER THREE MINUTES

131
00:11:34,902 --> 00:11:35,945
Hypocrite.

132
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:45,496
Why... Why does he hate me?

133
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:46,664
Sang-tae.

134
00:11:47,581 --> 00:11:49,083
Do as I say, please!

135
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:02,304
Sang-tae.

136
00:12:03,639 --> 00:12:04,640
Are you still mad?

137
00:12:09,645 --> 00:12:11,355
I'm sorry I yelled at you earlier.

138
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:13,983
I'll never do that again.

139
00:12:15,693 --> 00:12:16,610
Forgive me.

140
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:24,285
Sang-tae, please.

141
00:12:26,620 --> 00:12:27,663
That must hurt.

142
00:12:29,331 --> 00:12:30,541
You're hurting yourself.

143
00:12:32,501 --> 00:12:34,378
Someone slapped me in the face today.

144
00:12:37,506 --> 00:12:40,718
I was slapped so hard

145
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:43,637
that my gums bled,

146
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:47,349
and I can't even hear well.

147
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:52,605
My face is all swollen,
so I look like Mr. Lumpy now.

148
00:12:53,898 --> 00:12:55,816
-What do I do?
-"Mr. Lumpy"?

149
00:13:02,364 --> 00:13:05,284
Where's Mr. Lumpy? Mr. Lumpy.

150
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:08,871
My lumps are all gone.

151
00:13:10,831 --> 00:13:12,082
Gosh, I can't believe it.

152
00:13:19,965 --> 00:13:23,469
Lying is bad. It's deception.
The cops will arrest you.

153
00:13:23,552 --> 00:13:26,388
Pinocchio is bad.
The shepherd boy is also bad.

154
00:13:26,472 --> 00:13:28,599
Since you lied to me,
you deserve a scolding.

155
00:13:28,682 --> 00:13:31,644
You need a spanking.
Will you keep doing it knowing it's bad?

156
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:33,896
Answer me. Why are you all quiet?

157
00:13:33,979 --> 00:13:36,649
It's because you know you are bad.
Does it hurt?

158
00:13:45,241 --> 00:13:47,910
Have you... You haven't eaten yet, right?

159
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:49,495
Have a seat.

160
00:13:51,997 --> 00:13:53,499
Are you happy you got spanked?

161
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:55,501
Why do you keep asking for it?

162
00:13:55,584 --> 00:13:57,878
Are you doing this on purpose?

163
00:13:57,962 --> 00:14:00,005
I got what I deserved.

164
00:14:00,089 --> 00:14:01,090
Jeez.

165
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:04,009
All right. Come and eat.

166
00:14:04,343 --> 00:14:05,177
Come on.

167
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:07,263
No.

168
00:14:08,097 --> 00:14:09,473
What? What is it?

169
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:12,434
Well, would you mind...

170
00:14:17,773 --> 00:14:19,775
Are you hiding your wife somewhere here?

171
00:14:21,193 --> 00:14:23,737
-No, it's my landlady who's over 60.
-I could tell.

172
00:14:23,821 --> 00:14:25,239
She must be a seasoned cook.

173
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:26,490
Just eat.

174
00:14:45,801 --> 00:14:48,262
I want to live with this lady.
She's a great cook.

175
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:52,391
-What do you eat at home?
-I don't eat.

176
00:14:54,768 --> 00:14:56,896
I don't have a mom
who'd give me her limbs.

177
00:14:57,563 --> 00:14:59,273
At least you have a live-in cook.

178
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:03,152
Damn it.

179
00:15:29,053 --> 00:15:33,515
OK PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL

180
00:16:33,575 --> 00:16:34,827
Why are you standing here?

181
00:16:35,035 --> 00:16:37,496
Didn't you hear that sound just now?

182
00:16:38,455 --> 00:16:39,289
No.

183
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:42,418
The power is back on.

184
00:16:44,586 --> 00:16:47,339
I heard someone humming a song
from over there.

185
00:16:47,423 --> 00:16:49,591
Oh, that.

186
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:52,261
What exactly is "that"?

187
00:16:53,303 --> 00:16:54,972
Didn't Ms. Yoo Seon-hae tell you?

188
00:16:55,472 --> 00:16:59,101
Sometime after midnight,
you can hear a ghost humming a song

189
00:17:00,102 --> 00:17:02,771
at the end of the hallway
on the second floor.

190
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:10,154
I clearly heard it.

191
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:11,280
What? A ghost?

192
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:15,868
-She was probably talking nonsense, right?
-Well, I'm not sure.

193
00:17:16,744 --> 00:17:17,995
Ms. Yoo Seon-hae...

194
00:17:22,624 --> 00:17:25,586
has been making a living
communicating with ghosts.

195
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:27,212
What?

196
00:17:31,008 --> 00:17:32,301
She was a shaman.

197
00:17:38,223 --> 00:17:39,183
Wait up!

198
00:17:41,977 --> 00:17:43,520
I should make some coffee.

199
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:48,317
I saw nothing special while making rounds.

200
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,318
Okay, thanks.

201
00:17:51,153 --> 00:17:53,113
-Where's--
-He went to wash his face.

202
00:17:53,197 --> 00:17:54,490
-You sure?

203
00:17:56,784 --> 00:17:59,661
-Do you want some coffee?
-Sure, thank you.

204
00:17:59,745 --> 00:18:01,288
How are Mr. Ko Dae-hwan's vitals?

205
00:18:01,371 --> 00:18:03,624
His blood pressure is still
on the high side,

206
00:18:03,707 --> 00:18:05,584
and he's having some sleep disorders.

207
00:18:08,504 --> 00:18:10,130
Well, by the way...

208
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:15,094
-Earlier in the garden...
-Yes?

209
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:18,639
Why do you think he did that
to his daughter?

210
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:26,814
Some post-surgical complications
can result in sudden aggressive outbursts.

211
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:27,731
Here.

212
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:31,110
What if that wasn't the cause?

213
00:18:34,029 --> 00:18:36,698
Then what? Are you saying
he attacked her to kill her?

214
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:42,704
No.

215
00:18:43,997 --> 00:18:44,832
To live.

216
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:49,169
I mean, because he didn't want to die.

217
00:18:49,253 --> 00:18:52,589
If he became aggressive like that
to protect himself...

218
00:18:52,673 --> 00:18:54,174
Die!

219
00:18:55,884 --> 00:18:57,010
Ms. Nam.

220
00:18:58,178 --> 00:18:59,012
Yes?

221
00:19:01,098 --> 00:19:03,559
You said you and Ms. Ko Mun-yeong
know each other.

222
00:19:04,184 --> 00:19:05,018
Shall we

223
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:08,480
become friends?

224
00:19:08,564 --> 00:19:10,816
But you tried to hide it,

225
00:19:10,899 --> 00:19:13,152
which means you two aren't really
on good terms.

226
00:19:14,194 --> 00:19:16,196
Go away, please!

227
00:19:18,323 --> 00:19:19,158
Then now,

228
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:21,952
ask yourself this.

229
00:19:22,661 --> 00:19:25,873
Are you emotionally involving yourself
when it comes to those two?

230
00:19:26,373 --> 00:19:29,793
You shouldn't let countertransference
happen. You're a professional.

231
00:19:29,877 --> 00:19:33,130
A THERAPIST'S EMOTIONAL ENTANGLEMENT
WITH A CLIENT

232
00:20:02,910 --> 00:20:04,536
Finish it quick and lie down here.

233
00:20:06,788 --> 00:20:10,042
We must've been a servant
and a mistress in our past lives.

234
00:20:10,751 --> 00:20:13,378
You're working so hard.
You look scrumptious from behind.

235
00:20:16,506 --> 00:20:19,218
I mean, you look stunning,
not "scrumptious."

236
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:22,221
-My bad.
-Get up.

237
00:20:22,554 --> 00:20:26,141
-I'll give you money for a cab to go home.
-No, I'll sleep here tonight.

238
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:30,187
-Who says you can sleep here?
-I can do as I want.

239
00:20:30,771 --> 00:20:32,397
-Get up.
-No, I'll sleep here.

240
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:34,733
-I'll drag you out.
-You brought me here.

241
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:37,611
I never said you could sleep here.
Come on. Get up.

242
00:20:37,694 --> 00:20:39,696
You clothed me and fed me,
so let me sleep.

243
00:20:39,780 --> 00:20:42,616
-I'm not raising a newborn. Let go.
-Let go, or I'll scream.

244
00:20:42,699 --> 00:20:45,369
-Get out!
-Sang-tae!

245
00:20:49,206 --> 00:20:52,626
Hey, buddy! Let's have dinner together!

246
00:20:56,838 --> 00:20:59,716
Hey, why... Gosh, why did you come out?

247
00:20:59,967 --> 00:21:01,260
-Sorry, Jae-su.
-Jeez.

248
00:21:02,344 --> 00:21:05,055
Hey, why are you covered in sweat?

249
00:21:05,138 --> 00:21:08,308
Oh, my room is very hot.

250
00:21:08,642 --> 00:21:10,769
Gosh, it's so hot. You don't feel hot?

251
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:13,230
Hey, are you having hot flashes or what?

252
00:21:13,563 --> 00:21:16,483
You're acting so weird today.

253
00:21:18,860 --> 00:21:19,736
What do you mean?

254
00:21:21,738 --> 00:21:25,033
I thought you'd probably be eating
all alone looking sad,

255
00:21:25,117 --> 00:21:26,618
so I came to keep you company.

256
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:29,538
-Oh, I've already eaten.
-What? Already?

257
00:21:30,372 --> 00:21:32,958
Yes. Your food will get cold.
Go downstairs and eat.

258
