00:40:14,286 --> 00:40:16,497
What if he runs away?

518
00:40:16,956 --> 00:40:18,374
Chase him to the end.

519
00:40:19,625 --> 00:40:22,920
I, too, had to make such efforts
to bring you into this world.

520
00:40:27,675 --> 00:40:28,509
Here.

521
00:40:30,177 --> 00:40:33,139
But I must say, Mun-yeong has grown
into such a pretty lady.

522
00:40:33,222 --> 00:40:36,100
Pretty, my ass!

523
00:40:36,183 --> 00:40:37,643
She is not pretty.

524
00:40:38,227 --> 00:40:40,688
NEW SEONGJIN PUBLIC BATH

525
00:40:41,188 --> 00:40:43,774
Hey, will you please pick up your phone?

526
00:40:45,234 --> 00:40:46,068
Goodness.

527
00:40:53,576 --> 00:40:55,703
-Hello?
-Mr. Lee.

528
00:40:56,328 --> 00:40:58,289
-We're in trouble.
-I told you.

529
00:40:58,372 --> 00:41:01,625
Nothing's important to me
unless it's a life or death situation.

530
00:41:02,251 --> 00:41:04,086
We're all about to die.

531
00:41:05,045 --> 00:41:05,880
What?

532
00:41:05,963 --> 00:41:07,423
When you read someone's book,

533
00:41:07,756 --> 00:41:11,051
you can easily see
how that writer thinks and feels.

534
00:41:12,386 --> 00:41:16,307
Then I guess you also know
what I'm going to do next.

535
00:41:17,725 --> 00:41:20,269
But I, too, can attack you
with the tip of my pen.

536
00:41:20,352 --> 00:41:21,187
Goodbye.

537
00:41:29,361 --> 00:41:32,364
He got surgery for brain hemorrhage
and woke up in two days.

538
00:41:32,448 --> 00:41:34,742
No wonder he has been so quiet lately.

539
00:41:35,284 --> 00:41:36,785
Sir, take a look at this.

540
00:41:37,077 --> 00:41:39,955
He's demanding a huge amount
of compensation.

541
00:41:40,331 --> 00:41:41,332
If we don't comply,

542
00:41:41,415 --> 00:41:44,084
Ms. Ko will be arrested
or end up destroying her career.

543
00:41:44,502 --> 00:41:45,920
What should we do?

544
00:41:47,213 --> 00:41:49,298
Check how much cash we have...

545
00:41:49,381 --> 00:41:52,718
No, never mind.
Tell the accounting manager to join us.

546
00:41:54,053 --> 00:41:56,305
The manager quit a while ago
and can't be reached.

547
00:41:56,388 --> 00:41:58,766
Why didn't you tell me that earlier?

548
00:41:59,475 --> 00:42:00,893
You never asked.

549
00:42:02,353 --> 00:42:05,231
Sir, the printing house
and the distribution warehouse

550
00:42:05,314 --> 00:42:07,525
keep calling us
asking for the overdue payment.

551
00:42:07,608 --> 00:42:10,736
-How did things go at Seongjin City?
-Is she working on her next book?

552
00:42:10,819 --> 00:42:12,613
We're going to be okay, right?

553
00:42:14,698 --> 00:42:16,534
-Mr. Lee!
-Mr. Lee!

554
00:42:16,617 --> 00:42:17,868
-Sir, wake up!
-Mr. Lee!

555
00:42:17,952 --> 00:42:19,119
-Mr. Lee!
-Mr. Lee!

556
00:42:19,203 --> 00:42:21,247
-My gosh. Mr. Lee!
-Sir.

557
00:42:21,330 --> 00:42:22,331
Mr. Lee.

558
00:42:30,839 --> 00:42:33,425
-Are you okay, sir?
-Be quiet for a second. Hold on.

559
00:42:33,717 --> 00:42:34,593
Give me a minute.

560
00:42:58,075 --> 00:42:59,410
Gosh, no way.

561
00:43:04,331 --> 00:43:05,165
Seung-jae.

562
00:43:07,960 --> 00:43:08,961
Yes?

563
00:43:09,670 --> 00:43:11,171
Do you hike?

564
00:43:11,714 --> 00:43:12,631
Yes.

565
00:43:13,173 --> 00:43:15,467
I used to be the leader of a hiking club.

566
00:43:31,358 --> 00:43:32,568
Did you sleep with her?

567
00:43:35,321 --> 00:43:36,322
Are you guys dating?

568
00:43:40,701 --> 00:43:42,036
Do you like that lunatic?

569
00:43:46,332 --> 00:43:47,374
Are you drunk already?

570
00:43:49,710 --> 00:43:52,129
Then why did you ride Alberto
in the rain for her?

571
00:43:52,212 --> 00:43:54,673
Why did you bring her home
when you don't like her?

572
00:43:54,757 --> 00:43:58,344
Why feed her and let her sleep over?
Was it for charity? A new religion?

573
00:44:02,014 --> 00:44:03,349
The beer is a bit bland.

574
00:44:05,643 --> 00:44:06,602
Gang-tae,

575
00:44:07,061 --> 00:44:08,854
don't act out of the ordinary.

576
00:44:09,188 --> 00:44:13,400
-You'll die in the prism of your life.
-It's prime, not "prism."

577
00:44:18,155 --> 00:44:20,157
Anyway, you should be careful.

578
00:44:20,240 --> 00:44:21,408
Did you forget already?

579
00:44:21,742 --> 00:44:25,621
She hurt you with a knife
the first time you met her.

580
00:44:42,262 --> 00:44:43,097
Yes, she did.

581
00:44:45,057 --> 00:44:48,143
My gosh, are you reminiscing?
Is it taking you back and all?

582
00:44:50,437 --> 00:44:51,939
-What are you talking about?
-Hey.

583
00:44:52,022 --> 00:44:54,817
People who are insane
don't act based on logic.

584
00:44:54,900 --> 00:44:57,152
They turn into monsters
the moment they lose it.

585
00:44:57,236 --> 00:45:00,572
Look. Let this scar be a reminder.

586
00:45:00,656 --> 00:45:02,825
Next time, it might not be your hand.
Gosh…

587
00:45:03,826 --> 00:45:06,912
She might just go for your neck.

588
00:45:12,876 --> 00:45:13,711
You're right.

589
00:45:15,337 --> 00:45:16,672
I should avoid her, right?

590
00:45:16,755 --> 00:45:18,590
Of course. Don't ever get involved.

591
00:45:21,135 --> 00:45:23,011
I should stay out of her sight.

592
00:45:23,637 --> 00:45:26,473
Exactly. Don't even go near her.

593
00:45:32,020 --> 00:45:33,063
But the thing is,

594
00:45:41,613 --> 00:45:43,240
I am growing forgetful these days.

595
00:45:44,324 --> 00:45:46,034
-Forgetful about what?
-Everything.

596
00:45:49,246 --> 00:45:50,164
My scars.

597
00:45:51,957 --> 00:45:52,916
The butterflies.

598
00:45:56,670 --> 00:45:57,838
Even Sang-tae.

599
00:46:03,927 --> 00:46:05,637
I sometimes forget about them all.

600
00:46:10,392 --> 00:46:11,351
So

601
00:46:13,562 --> 00:46:15,063
you should remind me like this

602
00:46:17,107 --> 00:46:18,025
from time to time

603
00:46:20,569 --> 00:46:22,070
and help me come to my senses.

604
00:46:26,074 --> 00:46:26,992
Okay.

605
00:46:30,329 --> 00:46:32,039
I get it. So stop smiling like that.

606
00:46:35,292 --> 00:46:36,293
Why?

607
00:46:37,503 --> 00:46:39,087
-Do I look like Joker?
-No.

608
00:46:41,882 --> 00:46:43,008
You look like Chucky.

609
00:47:14,289 --> 00:47:17,167
I'm paying you back with money
for the love you showed me.

610
00:47:18,043 --> 00:47:19,419
It'll be enough for a ride.

611
00:47:23,257 --> 00:47:24,258
Damn it.

612
00:47:27,886 --> 00:47:31,265
Did he give me that to get rid of me?
Am I only worth 30,000 won?

613
00:47:32,391 --> 00:47:33,809
He lives like a poor beggar.

614
00:47:35,269 --> 00:47:37,563
That cheap jerk! How dare he?

615
00:47:38,230 --> 00:47:39,273
Darn it.

616
00:47:39,857 --> 00:47:40,899
Cheap jerk!

617
00:47:45,487 --> 00:47:46,321
That cheap jerk.

618
00:47:53,078 --> 00:47:53,912
Cheap jerk.

619
00:48:12,973 --> 00:48:13,974
My gosh.

620
00:48:15,392 --> 00:48:18,979
Why is he so fickle? It confuses me.
Does he have a split personality?

621
00:48:48,175 --> 00:48:50,385
Sang-tae, are you sleeping?

622
00:49:00,187 --> 00:49:03,357
Sang-tae, who do you like more?
Me or Ko Mun-yeong?

623
00:49:11,198 --> 00:49:13,116
I like you more.

624
00:49:16,703 --> 00:49:18,538
You're my everything.

625
00:49:43,772 --> 00:49:44,690
Who is it?

626
00:49:51,446 --> 00:49:52,280
Mun-yeong.

627
00:49:54,866 --> 00:49:55,826
We're doomed.

628
00:49:58,662 --> 00:49:59,538
Why is she here?

629
00:50:03,208 --> 00:50:04,042
I'm here

630
00:50:06,003 --> 00:50:08,171
because Mr. Lee tricked me
into coming here.

631
00:50:12,134 --> 00:50:13,844
With our company building deposit,

632
00:50:14,052 --> 00:50:16,930
I paid that darn Suicide Bomber
the money he asked for,

633
00:50:17,014 --> 00:50:19,349
gave our team the overdue salary
and severance pay,

634
00:50:19,433 --> 00:50:21,560
and paid all our subcontractors.

635
00:50:21,643 --> 00:50:24,563
-And now, I'm broke.
-You didn't give me my severance pay.

636
00:50:25,814 --> 00:50:28,775
You bought me this suitcase
and asked me to go on a business trip.

637
00:50:28,859 --> 00:50:30,402
-Are you a con artist?
-Hey!

638
00:50:30,736 --> 00:50:33,363
I brought you here
to take responsibility for your future.

639
00:50:33,447 --> 00:50:35,615
How will you do that
when you've gone bankrupt?

640
00:50:35,782 --> 00:50:38,076
Hey, I haven't gone bankrupt.

641
00:50:38,535 --> 00:50:41,580
I still have Ko Mun-yeong. She's my hope.

642
00:50:41,663 --> 00:50:42,581
Right?

643
00:50:42,914 --> 00:50:44,708
-Get out.
-This is so annoying.

644
00:50:45,917 --> 00:50:48,086
-Mun-yeong.
-Why do I have to save you

645
00:50:48,170 --> 00:50:49,421
from this mess you're in?

646
00:50:49,504 --> 00:50:52,257
Hey, come on.
Don't you know who caused this--

647
00:50:52,340 --> 00:50:53,675
You caused this to happen.

648
00:50:55,927 --> 00:50:57,262
Yes, that's right.

649
00:50:57,596 --> 00:50:59,514
It's all because I was an incompetent.

650
00:51:00,098 --> 00:51:01,892
-It's all my fault.
-Incompetent jerk.

651
00:51:01,975 --> 00:51:03,268
Now, leave.

652
00:51:04,102 --> 00:51:05,687
Mun-yeong, don't be like this.

653
00:51:05,771 --> 00:51:09,066
Just let me stay by your side
and help you publish your books.

654
00:51:09,149 --> 00:51:12,027
You even asked me to live with you.
Don't you remember?

655
00:51:12,527 --> 00:51:14,154
Didn't you run away?

656
00:51:15,322 --> 00:51:16,823
Someone else will move in here.

657
00:51:18,950 --> 00:51:19,785
Who?

658
00:51:21,578 --> 00:51:22,496
No way.

659
00:52:11,211 --> 00:52:15,298
OK PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL

660
00:52:18,844 --> 00:52:19,678
Young man.

661
00:52:20,512 --> 00:52:21,930
Hey, young man.

662
00:52:31,773 --> 00:52:32,607
Thank you.

663
00:52:42,993 --> 00:52:47,581
I've had my eyes on you
for the past couple of days.

664
00:52:49,833 --> 00:52:51,751
And I noticed that you're very handsome.

665
00:52:53,503 --> 00:52:56,214
You also have a nice build
and seem very reliable.

666
00:53:00,260 --> 00:53:01,303
EMPLOYEE CARD

667
00:53:01,386 --> 00:53:02,846
"Moon Gang-tae"?

668
00:53:03,930 --> 00:53:05,432
You also have a great name.

669
00:53:09,144 --> 00:53:09,978
How old are you?

670
00:53:10,937 --> 00:53:11,813
I'm 30 years old.

671
00:53:13,440 --> 00:53:14,649
What do your parents do?

672
00:53:17,485 --> 00:53:18,320
They're dead.

673
00:53:19,279 --> 00:53:20,322
Both of them?

674
00:53:22,407 --> 00:53:23,241
Oh, dear.

675
00:53:26,745 --> 00:53:28,079
Do you have a girlfriend?

676
00:53:31,833 --> 00:53:32,834
No.

677
00:53:35,086 --> 00:53:37,756
So that nurse has a crush on you?

678
00:53:38,757 --> 00:53:39,758
Pardon?

679
00:53:41,760 --> 00:53:42,594
That's good.

680
00:53:43,553 --> 00:53:44,679
What do you mean?

681
00:53:46,890 --> 00:53:50,727
I'd like to introduce you to a nice lady
who would be perfect for you.

682
00:53:52,604 --> 00:53:53,980
No, it's okay.

683
00:53:54,064 --> 00:53:55,774
It's not because she's my daughter.

684
00:53:56,608 --> 00:53:59,194
She really is a great catch.

685
00:54:00,237 --> 00:54:03,031
You should meet her
when she visits me one day.

686
00:54:03,323 --> 00:54:05,533
Well, I'll think about it.

687
00:54:06,243 --> 00:54:08,078
I need to get back to work.

688
00:54:09,746 --> 00:54:12,666
Let me know if you have a change of heart.

689
00:54:17,671 --> 00:54:20,006
They'll be a really good match.

690
00:54:31,935 --> 00:54:32,978
This isn't it.

691
00:54:36,481 --> 00:54:38,024
No.

692
00:54:43,238 --> 00:54:44,155
This isn't it.

693
00:54:55,166 --> 00:54:56,960
How about green?

694
00:55:01,923 --> 00:55:03,675
Gosh, no.

695
00:55:04,759 --> 00:55:05,593
This one?

696
00:55:07,220 --> 00:55:08,054
My goodness.

697
00:55:09,014 --> 00:55:12,809
The first step is always the hardest.

698
00:55:13,184 --> 00:55:16,396
But once you take your first step,
things will get easier from then on.

699
00:55:20,692 --> 00:55:25,071
Now, it's time for you to show me
what you're capable of.

700
00:55:26,823 --> 00:55:28,783
No, no! This isn't right!

701
00:55:28,867 --> 00:55:30,452
No!

702
00:55:30,535 --> 00:55:32,871
-I'm sorry.
-Why did you do that? That was bad.

703
00:55:32,954 --> 00:55:34,581
-Come here.
-I won't do it again.

704
00:55:34,664 --> 00:55:36,750
-Sang-tae.
-You can't do that.

705
00:55:36,833 --> 00:55:39,002
The director isn't sane either.
Don't you agree?

706
00:55:40,628 --> 00:55:43,673
Why are you crying again?
You promised you wouldn't cry.

707
00:55:43,757 --> 00:55:44,841
You ruined it.

708
00:55:44,924 --> 00:55:47,344
-A-reum.
-Because I'm jealous.

709
00:55:47,427 --> 00:55:49,554
I also want to play tag like that.

710
00:55:50,472 --> 00:55:53,767
Hold my hand. Let's go take your medicine.

711
00:55:54,100 --> 00:55:55,852
-You need to get scolded!
-No!

712
00:55:55,935 --> 00:55:57,645
Do you want to get scolded?

713
00:55:59,773 --> 00:56:00,607
It's funny

714
00:56:00,690 --> 00:56:03,818
how people who should be wearing
a patient gown aren't wearing one.

715
00:56:03,902 --> 00:56:06,738
-Why did you do that? Why?
-My goodness.

716
00:56:06,821 --> 00:56:08,198
Do you want to get scolded?

717
00:56:18,416 --> 00:56:19,334
Ms. Ko.

718
00:56:20,627 --> 00:56:21,503
How do you feel?

719
00:56:21,586 --> 00:56:23,380
Never good. Why did you call me?

720
00:56:26,674 --> 00:56:29,677
I heard what your father did to you.
I'm very sorry.

721
00:56:31,221 --> 00:56:32,764
It wasn't you who strangled me.

722
00:56:32,847 --> 00:56:35,725
But still, I was the one who told you
to take him out for walks.

723
00:56:35,809 --> 00:56:38,645
Then it was a medical accident.
You can't just end it

724
00:56:38,728 --> 00:56:40,313
with an apology.

725
00:56:44,025 --> 00:56:45,193
Then let's do this.

726
00:56:46,653 --> 00:56:49,030
You can strangle me instead.
Here. Go ahead.

727
00:56:51,658 --> 00:56:53,952
What a crazy old man.

728
00:56:57,664 --> 00:56:59,457
The sound of a ghost humming?

729
00:57:00,583 --> 00:57:01,418
Yes.

730
00:57:01,793 --> 00:57:05,839
By any chance, do you know what time
it was when you heard that last night?

731
00:57:08,174 --> 00:57:09,008
I don't know.

732
00:57:09,634 --> 00:57:11,761
I don't even know what date it is today.

733
00:57:12,220 --> 00:57:14,389
I just heard it on my way to the bathroom.

734
00:57:17,559 --> 00:57:20,812
Then did you happen to see anyone
in front of room 203

735
00:57:20,895 --> 00:57:23,106
or in the hallway?

736
00:57:24,858 --> 00:57:27,986
She said it was a ghost humming,
so it was probably a ghost.

737
00:57:30,780 --> 00:57:32,157
Ms. Nam.

738
00:57:33,408 --> 00:57:36,786
-Do you believe her gibberish?
-It's not gibberish.

739
00:57:37,704 --> 00:57:39,539
I swear I can hear it.

740
00:57:39,622 --> 00:57:43,835
That's called auditory hallucination.
And it's proof that you're crazy.

741
00:57:46,004 --> 00:57:48,506
Hey, I'm not crazy.

742
00:57:48,965 --> 00:57:51,009
Yes, I'm sure you heard what you heard.

743
00:57:56,473 --> 00:57:59,017
Then are you saying I'm crazy?

744
00:58:31,424 --> 00:58:33,051
Standing here with you like this

745
00:58:34,427 --> 00:58:35,678
reminds me of the past.

746
00:58:38,515 --> 00:58:40,350
Do you remember what you said to me,

747
00:58:40,767 --> 00:58:43,603
crying on the rooftop
after getting slapped by a patient?

748
00:58:44,729 --> 00:58:46,147
back at Yongrim Hospital?

749
00:58:47,232 --> 00:58:50,568
"Why don't you slap me
and make yourself feel better?"

750
00:58:55,031 --> 00:58:56,699
I didn't know you'd really slap me.

751
00:58:56,783 --> 00:58:58,868
I must've been crazy. Why did I do that?

752
00:59:03,831 --> 00:59:07,585
But thanks to that,
we became really close, didn't we?

753
00:59:13,466 --> 00:59:14,300
Or are we not?

754
00:59:16,844 --> 00:59:18,096
Are we not close?

755
00:59:20,807 --> 00:59:21,766
Ju-ri.

756
00:59:27,897 --> 00:59:29,440
Do you want to slap me again?

757
00:59:32,068 --> 00:59:32,902
Why?

758
00:59:33,653 --> 00:59:37,240
Because I feel like you'll get upset
in a little while.

759
00:59:46,416 --> 00:59:47,250
Are you

760
00:59:48,960 --> 00:59:50,503
rejecting me already?

761
00:59:51,129 --> 00:59:52,255
Don't bother

762
00:59:54,173 --> 00:59:55,592
wasting your emotions on me.

763
00:59:57,343 --> 00:59:58,761
I don't deserve any of that.

764
00:59:59,554 --> 01:00:00,805
Because

765
01:00:02,473 --> 01:00:04,017
you're going to leave anyway?

766
01:00:07,061 --> 01:00:09,147
It doesn't matter. Just...

767
01:00:11,065 --> 01:00:14,277
Just let me keep liking you.
That's up to me.

768
01:00:22,493 --> 01:00:23,911
Do me a favor.

769
01:00:29,250 --> 01:00:30,209
I hope

770
01:00:33,630 --> 01:00:35,465
you don't run away

771
01:00:37,592 --> 01:00:40,678
because you find me uncomfortable.

772
01:00:41,638 --> 01:00:42,472
If you do,

773
01:00:43,681 --> 01:00:47,602
it'll make me feel really pathetic

774
01:00:53,941 --> 01:00:55,234
and sad.

775
01:00:58,029 --> 01:01:00,657
Just continue to live with us at our house

776
01:01:02,325 --> 01:01:03,826
while you're in Seongjin City.

777
01:01:08,581 --> 01:01:11,250
My mom really likes you guys.

